    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "The <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">UVIndex</code> class simulates UV risk warnings for a number of days.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">UVIndex.java</code>, complete the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">generateWarnings()</code> method to return a list of UV warnings, one per day, using a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">for</code> loop.\r\n\r\nEach warning should look like this:\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #ececec; padding: 8px;\">Day 1: Wear sunscreen!</pre>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Use a loop to count from 1 to the number of days and build the string line by line.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n## ***Don't forget to . . .***\r\n![](https://images.code.org/eb2c8910ae2e150019b8e2177405d4af-image-1668191576873.png)\r\n",
